<header class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">The way out</div>
    <h1>A building doesn't have to go to the market.<br>It can go to the <span>people who live in it</span>.</h1>
    <p class="deck">
      When a landlord sells an expiring building, everyone assumes the only question is which
      investor buys it. That's not true, it has never been true, and there are buildings in this
      city that prove it.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">

    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Two buildings, two endings</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      I want to show you two buildings. Both housed low-income New Yorkers in New York City.
      Both were fought for. The only difference is what happened to the ownership — and it
      decided everything.
    </p>

